Background: In January 2024, we launched a program to reduce onboarding time-to-value (TTV) by 20% and improve NPS for new customers. Baseline TTV was 62 days with NPS +31. 
Findings: By June, median TTV decreased to 45 days (-27%), exceeding the target. NPS improved to +41, with the largest gains in enterprise accounts (+14 points). Key drivers included (1) standardized project plans released Feb 12, (2) integration wizard v1 deployed March 20, cutting SSO setup from 8 hours to 3, and (3) weekly executive check-ins for high-ARR customers. Support ticket backlog for new implementations dropped 32%. 
Operational Metrics: 78% of projects hit phase 1 by Day 14 (vs. 52% baseline). On-time go-lives rose from 71% to 86%. Average PS hours per implementation fell from 84 to 67, producing an estimated $420K cost avoidance in H1. 
Recommendations: 
1) Standardize onboarding playbooks across three tiers by July 31; 
2) Invest $180K in integration tooling (v2) to automate user provisioning and data mapping; 
3) Formalize executive sponsor program for accounts >$300K ARR; 
4) Expand customer education with role-based modules. 
Risks: Tooling backlog could delay v2 to Q4; resource constraints in EMEA may cap throughput. 
Expected Impact: A further 10–15% reduction in PS hours and +4–6 NPS points in H2 if funded.
